tid="author" dir="auto" class="xkz0k9k xyiysdx xe9ewy2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 xlyipyv xuxw1ft xnpuxes" style="min-height: 0px;">Priest</span></div><div></div><div class="x104kibb x1ul5b45 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1ezpfd3 x1n6pog2 xhslqc4 xlyipyv xj0a0fe x126k92a x1h7i4cw x1ua5tub" dir="ltr" role="button"><span data-testid="selectable-text" dir="auto" class="quoted-mention xnpuxes selectable-text copyable-text" style="min-height: 0px;">I will agree with you about adjourning till Monday. I see that the programmer is still working on the website. We have a couple of dead buttons that are in place currently I believe under governance. And I noticed some of the videos aren’t there just yet and I noticed the foundation logo with the spinning earth is not being displayed just yet.

After your careful review of the documents once they’re uploaded; I need to send the following
F 1023
F 56
Trademark paperwork</span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="x1n2onr6 x1mzt3pk x126k92a x6ikm8r x10wlt62"><span data-testid="selectable-text" dir="ltr" class="x1f6kntn xjb2p0i x8r4c90 xo1l8bm x1ic7a3i x12xpedu xnpuxes selectable-text copyable-text" style="min-height: 0px;"><span class="x1lliihq">I agree that adjourning until Monday would be the most practical approach. After reviewing the website, I can confirm that the recent adjustments are part of the ongoing implementation and development process. I observed that additional images have already been uploaded and several modifications have been made, which indicates that work is actively progressing behind the scenes.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
</span><span class="x1lliihq">The inactive buttons, missing videos, and the Foundation logo with the spinning earth animation are all items that appear to be part of the current development phase. At this time, there is no cause for alarm. I am confident that the programmer is aware of these outstanding items and will address them as part of the implementation process before the final deployment stage.
</span><span class="x1lliihq">
